INSTALL & START
    1. install angular on your computer:
       npm install -g @angular/cli (if no angular cli in computer)

    2. create a new angualr app:
       ng create appName

    3. start or stop your live server:
       start: npm start  or ng serve
       stop: CTRL + C


CREATE A COMPONENT:
    1. create a component in your app:
       ng generate component root/newComponentName

       SHORT WAY:
       ng g c root/newComponentName

    2. if you dont want some kind of file when create componment:
       add --fileAttribute==false after the newComponentName
       Example:
       ng g c root/newComponentName --fileAttribute==false.


ADD BOOTSTRAP:
    1. npm install npm install bootstrap @4.0.0-beta.2 jquery poper.js

    2. go to angular.json file:
        1. find styles[] add:
        "./node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.css"
        
        2. find scripts[] add:
        "./node_modules/jquery/dist/jquery.js",
        "./node_modules/popper.js/dist/umd/popper.js",
        "./node_modules/bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.js"

        3. restart server


ADD FONTAWESOME:
     1. npm install font-awesome

     2. go to angular.json file:
        1. find styles[] add:
        "./node_modules/font-awesome/css/font-awesome.css"